{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Having It Off | image = | caption = | genre = [[Situation comedy]] | creator = | starring = [[Antony Cotton]] | country = United Kingdom | language = English | num_series = 1 | num_episodes = 6 | executive_producer = | producer = | camera = | runtime = 30 minutes | network = [[BBC Choice]] | picture_format = 4:3 | first_aired = 2002 | last_aired = }}
'''''Having it Off''''' is a one-off TV comedy series for [[BBC Choice]] made by [[Red Production Company]] in 2002.
It was set at a cheap hairdressing salon in [[Eccles, Greater Manchester|Eccles]], [[Greater Manchester]]. It was shown only once and is not available yet on [[DVD]].
Out [[gay]] bitchy stereotype Guy La Trousse (played by [[Antony Cotton]], ''[[Coronation Street]]'', ''[[Queer as Folk (UK TV series)|Queer As Folk]]''), desperately tries to escape the drudge of daily wash and crop and change the fortunes of the salon - and his career.
This is all thwarted by April, nymphomanic loud-mouthed wife of the hairdressers owner.
The BBC website describes it as "rude, crude, strongly working-class sitcom on the lesser-seen BBC Choice, ''Having It Off'' promised much yet fell curiously short of the mark, lacking the key that would have propelled it to a higher level". However, tapes have been known to change hands on [[eBay]] for high prices.
