'''Orazio di Santis''' (active 1568&ndash;1577) was an [[Italy|Italian]] engraver of the [[Renaissance]] period. He was probably born in [[L'Aquila]]. He made prints based on designs of [[Pompeo Aquilano]]. Also 74 plates of antique statues in [[Rome]], the joint work of Santis and [[Cherubino Alberti]], published in 1584.

